Job Description
Share
The AFOM will manage all Front Office operations to include, but not limited to, guest service and registration (check-in/check-out), room inventory and availability, guest service standards, product quality, cost controls and overall profitability, marketing initiatives, systems use, management, budgeting and forecasting
Monitor staff performance , provide supervision, evaluations and deliver recognition and reward
OPERA knowledge is required
Monitor and assess service and satisfaction trends, evaluate and address issues and make improvements accordingly
Meet and greet guests and respond to guest inquiries, requests and issues in a timely, friendly and efficient manner and resolves guest concerns
Ensure staff have current knowledge of hotel products, services, facilities, events, pricing and policies and knowledge of the local area and events
Desired Candidate Profile
Skills: Excellent interpersonal skills, Committed to delivering a high level of customer service, career oriented and ability to work under pressure.
Experience: 3-4 years experience at Front Desk
Keyword: Assistant FOM
